==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek [[Anna]]. [[Anna]] is the Greek form of the Hebrew female name [[Hannah]], meaning 'grace; gracious'. Cf. [[Johannes]], [[Hannibal]].

===Proper noun===
'''Ann'''
# A female [[given name]].

